<br>
We hunted night after night in Lower Guk, and slowly, I became part of their little family. At the time, I had just exited my previous guild, House of Serenity, because the guild was shut down. (The leader disbanded it due to RL stress) So here we were, a near full group of friends in search of a guild. We continued to hunt together, and one night, Rangen told me about a lady named Heather, and her family called Aquilo Ferox. He told me I should speak to her and see if I could get invited to join them, because Rangen, Phordin, Dukalek, and Advid were all doing the same. So I did, and a few days later, I was invited by Heather into Aquilo Ferox.<br>
<br>
This is when Aalaandro was born really...from that day on, I've grown with the guild, seen it in every shape, size, strength, I've seen it appear to die, then be rebourn, then die again, then come back. The idea of the guild will never die, even if one day the guild no longer exists.<br>
<br>
This isn't much of a story, but the main part of it is that without meeting Rangen that night, I might never have had a group with them, might never have met Heather, might never have joined Aquilo, and might never have known many of those whom I consider my best friends, and might never have met the woman I call my wife. So as much as this was a story, it is a way of saying thanks to everyone in my family, and all those who've made me who I am.<br>
<br>
Splos, you are unbelievable...when I think I've forgotten something, you manage to refresh my memories.<br>
<br>
Miraa, I think I remember that PoF break..you had an afk message of &quot;Can't talk now, being woo'd&quot; Or something similar as you were alone with Splos in the Plane of Fear....<br>
